  === TrustZone / Secure World

  - #link("https://developer.arm.com/documentation/100935/0100/The-TrustZone-hardware-architecture-?lang=en")[TrustZone]
    is an ARM-only hardware isolation mechanism

  - It is implemented on the
    #link("https://developer.arm.com/Architectures/A-Profile%20Architecture")[Application(A)-profiles]
    of ARMv7-9, this is what we discuss

  - Also implemented on the ARMv7-M (Microcontroller) profile, but
    differently

  - Splits the system into 2 #strong[worlds]: Secure and non-Secure

  - They are also called #strong[Trusted] / #strong[Rich] Execution
    Environment (TEE/REE)

  - This is #strong[orthogonal] to Exception Levels:

    - EL3 (Secure Monitor) only exists in #strong[Secure] world

    - EL2, if it exists, can exist in #strong[Secure],
      #strong[Non-Secure], or both

    - EL1 and EL0 must exist in #strong[both] security states

